    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs required 3) is accepted given that the ASTM F1717 standard configuration is the sole regulatory reference condition and model influence is Medium. E/uval ratios for all three primary QoIs are below 1.96 and percentage differences are below 10%. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support use of the FEA framework for the non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending COU at Medium assurance level.",
